The President of Russia Vladimir Putin signed the law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for the violation of the time and order of payment of goods (works, services) when making purchases for state and municipal needs.
This law is intended to solve a very acute problem of non-fulfillment of its obligations by customers in the execution of state and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation, when entrepreneurs could not receive payment for already executed state and municipal contracts, was ubiquitous.
At the same time, the President of Russia gave orders to the Prosecutor General’s Office of the Russian Federation to take the problem under special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unfair customers, who concluded contracts that were not supported by financing, tried to avoid the commitments made on payment and included in the contracts illegal conditions.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in the interest of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment for public orders by the prosecutor’s office, 9.7 thousand submissions have been made, as a result of their consideration of disciplinary responsibility, 4,5 thousand employees have been brought to the office of public officials, to the administrative office, to the office of representatives - 533, in the investigative bodies for the organization.
As a result, debts to entrepreneurs amounting to more than 66 billion rubles were paid off.
And these huge sums were accumulated far from the non-payment of multi-billion-dollar contracts.
Fascinating debts have led to numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs for much more modest amounts.
Here's a typical case.
The manager of a small company won the competition for the provision of services on social transport for several million rubles.
The person invested all his working capital, fully fulfilled his obligations, but did not receive the deposited money in time.
The result is a growing financial coma of debts on salaries, taxes, loans that would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur did not seek help from the prosecutor.
At present, the problem has been minimized as much as possible in a number of regions.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt under state and municipal contracts, identified by prosecutors of entities of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where indebtedness rates continue to reach critical levels, the prosecutor’s office operates in a manual anti-crisis management mode.
The Prosecutor-General personally conducts outbound meetings with representatives of the local authority, which deal with all the violations identified by the prosecutors and measures for their immediate elimination.
Such operational meetings have already been held this year in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg.
Qualitatively to improve the payment discipline of the subordinates of public customers will be able to implement the Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offences in Part of the Establishment of Administrative Liability of the Officials of the Client".
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia at the initiative of the Prosecutor General’s Office.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on administrative offences with an article, which provides for a fine of 30 thousand to 50,000 rubles for violation by the official of the customer of the time and order of payment of goods, works and services in state and municipal procurement.
And if the official has already been subject to an administrative penalty for a similar offence, then he will be disqualified for a period of one year to two years.
All prosecutors of the subjects of the Russian Federation have already received an order to ensure the application of these legislative novelles in practice.
