Locals want more foreign governments to pay attention to the situation.
When an official delegation from the Netherlands, led by Dutch Ambassador for Human Rights Kiis Van Baar, visited Jayapur on May 4, locals broke the silence, pleading: “We want freedom”, as a source who was also present at the meeting stated.
Indonesia will hold new presidential elections in 2019, but the Papuans say they are unlikely to vote for the Jokovi again.
