Everyone must do everything right, not only for the sake of the play, but also for the sake of the memory of the four people killed.
The scene starts at first.
This time, when Rascon says the word on the letter "n," it becomes clear and sharp.
No one laughs.
The show ends brutally and quickly.
Screams, shots, and then silence.
