Her voice is interrupted by the word.
In a hundred yards from it, half a hundred spectators wipe tears and sweat from their eyes.
The number of spectators is almost equal to the number of blacks and whites.
One couple came from Ithaca, New York, to see the show; many live very close by.
They all endured Georgia’s heavy thirst for nearly eight hours while Brooks led them on a pilgrimage to the graves of Malcolm and Dorsey.
Until then, the murders remained only a story, but now that they are standing in the same place where people were lynching, it seems that their ghosts are blowing right in the air.
