The order and place of the oath will be determined by the President
Where and how new Russian citizens will swear allegiance to the Russian Federation will be determined by the president - such amendments to the second reading of the relevant law have been developed by the State Duma Committee on Legislation and State Construction.
A week ago, the deputies planned to directly determine the procedure for taking an oath in the law.
Children under the age of 18 will be released from the solemn oath, as well as the incapacitated, follows from the revised text of the amendments to the draft law "On citizenship of the Russian Federation" (there is at the disposal of "Izvestia"), which the committee will consider on July 11 before its second reading.
President Vladimir Putin supported the idea of introducing an oath when entering into the citizenship of the Russian Federation instead of formally signing the documents during a meeting on June 6 with the Speaker of the State Duma Vyacheslav Volodymyr.
The deputies have formulated this idea in the form of an amendment to the second reading of the draft law, which provides for the annulment of the decision on the issue of citizenship to those who were subsequently convicted of a number of crimes of a terrorist or extremist nature.
According to the bill, his logic was as follows: by filing documents for citizenship, a person is signed under a promise to comply with Russian legislation - stood on the path of extremism, he violates this promise.
The bill was introduced in the State Duma in April by the leaders of the Duma factions Vladimir Vasilyev ("United Russia"), Gennadiy Zuganov (CPRF), Vladimir Zhirinovsky (LDPR), Sergey Mironov ("Just Russia") and the speaker of DG Vochev.
On May 19, the deputies adopted it in the first reading.
Last week, the DG Committee on State Construction and Legislation approved the text of the bill for a second reading, but it has now been revised again.
Now it says that the procedure for taking the oath will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Earlier, parliamentarians were going to describe the procedure directly in the law "On Russian citizenship", stating that the ceremony should be held in a ceremonial setting in front of the state coat of arms and the flag of Russia in the presence of a representative of the Ministry of Interior.
However, it was not clear from the text of the draft law where such an event should take place - the list of places where it is possible to place the coat of arms of the Russian Federation, regulated by the relevant federal constitutional law.
These include courts, offices of heads of state bodies of subjects, municipal entities, judges, prosecutors, heads of federal executive bodies, etc.
Most likely, it could also be the SATs.
To make a solemn oath those wishing to obtain the citizenship of the Russian Federation will after the officials check their documents.
But a Russian passport a person will receive only after taking an oath, follows from the revised text.
A week ago, the draft said that the oath should precede the signing of the decree.
The updated text says that Russia will be sworn in from the age of 18, not from the age of 14.
There is a rule which exempts those who are incapacitated or incapacitated, as well as those who cannot pronounce, read or hand-sign the oath.
In addition, the President of the Russian Federation has the right to exempt from this procedure and "other persons",
Also, the updated bill stipulates a special procedure for the admission of Russian citizens of Ukraine, who are considered to be holders of the Russian language.
They will have to formally renounce Ukrainian citizenship by submitting a corresponding application to the authorized body of Ukraine for this purpose.
A notarized copy of the statement will have to be transmitted to Russian officials.
The renunciation of “foreign” citizenship, as it is now, will not be required if it is provided for by an international treaty or if it is not possible “for reasons not dependent on the person”.
The corresponding amendment to the law was proposed by a group of deputies, among them the first vice-speaker of DG Ivan Melnikov (CPRF), Natalya Poklonskaya, Pavel Krasheninnikov and Ayrat Farrahov (all - "United Russia").
I think many of you know that getting a reference from Ukraine is unrealistic, just impossible.
Accordingly, a lot of people are waiting for a solution of their fate regarding the citizenship of the Russian Federation, - explained the head of the Duma Committee on State Construction and Legislation Pavel Krasheninnikov (ER).
In addition, the text clarified that the restrictions on the employment of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who have given up their "other" citizenship in writing and handed over their former passport to the Ministry of Interior of Russia, but "for reasons not dependent on it" did not cease to be considered foreign citizens.
It is now forbidden for foreigners to hold positions in the municipal service, to be admitted to work at facilities and in organizations whose activities are related to the security of Russia.
Also, a person with dual citizenship or residence permit of another country may not become a State Duma Member or a member of the Federation Council.
It is planned that the law will enter into force from September 1, 2017, by which time the necessary legislative acts must be prepared.
