I do not know what the scheme will be, I do not deal directly with these issues.
In fact, the economy for Russia in Libya is not important.
We are, in fact, engaged in peacekeeping work.
The main thing for us is to stop the bloodshed, help the Libyans to agree among themselves so that they can establish order and Libya has ceased to be a favorable environment for the development of terrorism.
For Russia, this is the main task – to help the Libyan people and to expel the terrorists from there.
Do you have any information about the presence in Libya (now or before) of radical militants from Russia or other countries of the former USSR?
