Which country are these fighters from?
I would not like to go into these details.
Then we formulate the question differently.
How many of the Islamist militants in Libya are the Libyans themselves?
There are almost no Libyans among them, they are no more than 5%.
The rest are aliens.
Can Moscow hold intra-Libyan negotiations on the example of Paris?
There are such plans.
We are actively negotiating with the Libyans, several delegations from Libya have already visited Moscow, and have said they are ready to come again - to Moscow or to the Terrible.
When can such negotiations take place?
It's hard to say now.
Several more visits are yet to be made, and then I hope there will be clarity about the time and place of negotiations.
