In the new capacity, he will try himself one of the best academic chamber orchestras "Musica Viva" under the direction of Alexander Rudin and with the participation of pianist Yuri Favorin.
The merging of jazz, ethnic and electronic music, as well as academic traditions, will demonstrate the ensemble "Marimba Plus" and its leader, composer and performer at the marimba Leah Slepner.
One of the most unusual festival performances promises to be a set of award winner Sergei Kurehin Anton Maskeliadze.
The artist-experimenter manages music and video with gestures – that’s how the leap motion technology works.
In total, eight musical groups will perform on two stages of the festival.
In addition, the program includes open discussions, interactive zones and art objects, combined by the idea of the merging of music and science.
Guests will be able to take part in experiments, visit the scientific buffet and observe the creation of cryo-frozen or flaky sands from starch and water.
In the special zone of vinyl it will be possible to purchase records of relevant jazz performers and representatives of other musical directions, and at the book fair - publications on various topics, including musical, scientific and popular and biomedical literature.
