In Russia, two new territories of precursor socio-economic development will appear - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR are defined on the territory of the city of Abbaza in the Republic of Hakassia.
In the city, where 15,000 people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
In the list of types of economic activity, in which the company "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, include plant breeding, livestock, the production of food, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-building enterprise of OOO "Abakan Mining".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Hakasiya fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
Similarly, the authorities of the Orenburg region did.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk will also be created the territory of the preceding socio-economic development.
This will diversify the economy of the monopolist, reduce its dependence on the city-building enterprise of JSC Ural Steel, as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of types of economic activity in which the new TOR will operate a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fisheries, the production of feed, pharmaceuticals and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monotowns of the Orenburg region to receive TOR status.
Recall that the territory of pre-development is an economic zone with favourable tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment to improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for TOR residents can be distinguished the following: a profit tax of not more than 5% in the first five years, and not less than 10% in the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% in the amount of income in the form of income for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, the preferential regime.
